---

Preheat your oven to 200°C and remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} from the fridge
and allow them to come up to room temperature. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 2cm slices,
then chop into 2cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large, low-sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot,
roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the chips nicely spread out.

Pick the @tarragon{1}(leaves picked from stalks, roughly chopped, stalks discarded) and
roughly chop. Pop the @wild rocket{40%g} into a large #bowl{} (we'll dress this later).

15 mins before the chips are done, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high
heat. When the oil is hot, lay the steaks into the pan. Season them with @salt{} and
@pepper{} and fry until browned, ~{1%minute} on each side. Lower the heat slightly and cook
for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want them medium-rare.

> Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more cooked.

Once cooked, remove to a #board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat
> when the outside is browned.

Whilst the steak rests, return the frying pan (no need to wipe) to a medium-high heat.
Add the @water{100%ml} for the sauce and stir in the @wild mushroom paste{15%g}. Bring it to a
simmer then stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and chopped tarragon. Simmer for
~{1%minute} and remove from the heat. When the sauce is ready, slice the rested steaks
widthways into 1cm slices.

Once everything is ready, reheat the sauce if necessary. Add the @French dressing{30%ml} to the
rocket and mix well to coat. Transfer the steaks to your plates and pour over the creamy
tarragon sauce. Serve with the chips and rocket salad alongside. Enjoy!